post_title: The Game Awards Disaster
author: @JohnSchaeffer-u4i
text: I think the problem is that the Game Awards are structured like the Oscars. The categories themselves are the problem. Most of the awards are like awards for movies. So certain games will always have massive advantages. If you are a realistic, cinematic, story heavy game, you're going to be nominated in like every category. There should be more actual "gamey" categories. Like best combat system, best boss fights, best control scheme. But no. Games want to be movies so badly. And Geoff wants the Game Awards to just be the Oscars.
